The paper discusses the application of deep learning for channel estimation in wireless networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of deep learning also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on future wireless systems, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
